  "title": "Process Engineer (East)",
  "description": "<ul>\n  <li>Adhere to the overall project timeline and workflow set by the project team.</li>\n  <li>Provide feedback on professional design methodologies and standards.</li>\n  <li>Train and guide fellow project mechanical engineers, assistant engineers (AEs), and drafters to collaborate effectively.</li>\n  <li>Analyze and resolve project-related issues within the scope of mechanical engineering responsibilities.</li>\n  <li>Report on project design data, including object quantities and technical parameters.</li>\n  <li>Participate in and provide updates during project and departmental meetings.</li>\n  <li>Complete assigned tasks related to project drawings and documentation in a timely manner.</li>\n  <li>Prepare and review marine machinery and piping calculations, specifications, and vendor drawings.</li>\n  <li>Prepare and review 2D arrangement drawings and schematic designs for marine machinery and piping systems, including submission materials.</li>\n  <li>Develop and review 3D models and related production/site support drawings for marine machinery and piping systems.</li>\n  <li>Provide technical support to the Project Section Lead on mechanical engineering issues.</li>\n  <li>Coordinate effectively with shipyards, consultants, vendors, and other stakeholders.</li>\n  <li>Report to the Mechanical Project Section Lead and Mechanical Technical Lead.</li>\n  <li>Handle various types of projects, including new builds, repairs, upgrades, and conversions.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>We regret only shortlisted candidates will be contacted. All applications will be handled confidentially. By submitting your application, you agree to the collection, use, retention, and disclosure of your personal information to prospective employers.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>Wecruit Pte Ltd</p>\n<p>EA License No: 20C0270</p>",
